   Town Manager: Paul Nordin

   [BrushStroke.gif]

   [PNordin.jpg] Paul has been active in city/town management for the past
   15 years. He continues to serve as the first Town Manager of Fountain
   Hills, Arizona, a position he has held since June of 1990. Prior to his
   service here, Paul was the City Manager of Benson, Arizona; and has
   also served as an Assistant Manager for two communities in Kansas. Paul
   teaches a city/county management class at Arizona State University, a
   position he has held for five years. He is the only person to receive
   the "Excellence In Teaching Award" two years in a row. He has also
   received the Outstanding Faculty Award from the College of Extended
   Education at ASU. He serves as the Chairman for the Esser/Andrews
   Scholarship Awards Committee for Arizona City/County Management
   Association and the State Representative to the national Task Force for
   Continuing Education and Professional Development for City Management.
   Paul is an active member of the International City Management
   Association and Maricopa Association of Governments Management
   Committee. Paul holds a Masters in Public Administration and Bachelors
   in Political Science, both from Brigham Young University.

   Send Email to: pnordin@fh.az.gov
